Seyi Shay has released a new track titled Ko Ma Roll in which she features Tanzanian singer Harmonize. The Afropop queen’s track will definitely make fans roll on the dance floor. Born Deborah Oluwaseyi Joshua on December 21st, 1985, Seyi Shay was groomed for stardom at an early age. She started singing at the age of six and booked her first professional gig in high school as a member of the London Community Gospel Choir during a world tour that included 13 cities in Japan. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-812858 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="1233" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1.jpeg 1080w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1-621x598.jpeg 621w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1-487x469.jpeg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1-974x938.jpeg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1-249x240.jpeg 249w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1-498x480.jpeg 498w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/WhatsApp-Image-2018-12-14-at-5.57.56-PM-1-600x578.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Seyi Shay went on to study Performing Arts as an A-Level and went on to study Business Management at the University of East London. Aged eighteen, she signed her first record deal with Sir George Martin – the producer of the legendary band, The Beatles. Seyi wrote three major songs for the Konami Game Soundtrack “Crime Life”, as well as the song “You will see” performed by former Spice Girl Mel C and included in her highly successful album “Beautiful Intentions”. After a highly publicized national audition in the United Kingdom, Seyi Shay emerged lead singer of the British Pop/RnB girl-band, ‘From Above’. The band was signed to Sony/Columbia Records and Music World Entertainment owned by Beyoncé’s father Matthew Knowles. Led by Seyi Shay, the group supported Beyoncé in 5 cities on her “I AM” UK tour in 2009/10, and presented the Best New Act award to Bruno Mars at the MTV EMA music awards in 2011. Also in 2011, Seyi wrote the song ‘White Lies’ for rapper/artist Chipmunk which featured Coleena of P.Diddy’s Dirty Money group.
Listen to the track below. https://itunes.apple.com/ng/album/koma-roll-feat-harmonize-single/1446871792